" Little Miss Fix It," the vehicle chosen for the metropolitan reappearance of Nora Bayes and Jack Norworth, which took place at the Globe Theatre last evening, has no more plot than the average Broadway musical comedy, which it is not, and not half so many vaudeville specialties to fill in the time.
